         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Aug 15 /84 ¶ Dear Baron ¶  ¶ I write to say that the  ¶ Dendrobium superbiens ¶ , Fitzgerald quite distinct from the plant of Rchb fil ¶  ¶ Thanks for  ¶ Latourea ¶  you are no doubt right. ¶  ¶ Am gl...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.08.15b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS embossed with crest of Royal Gardens Kew.</p>
               </note>Aug 15 /84</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hooker is responding to questions and comments in <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to J. Hooker, 25 June 1884 (in this edition as 84-06-25a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I write to say that the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Dendrobium%20superbiens">Dendrobium superbiens</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>, Fitzgerald quite distinct from the plant of Rchb fil<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Reichenbach (1876) described <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Dendrobium%20superbiens">Dendrobium superbiens</name>
                     </seg>. Cf. Fitzgerald's illustration of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Dendrobium%20superbiens">Dendrobium superbiens</name>, </seg>
                     <seg style="">the name of which he</seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>attributes to Reichenbach (R. Fitzgerald (1875-94), vol. 2, part 1, plate [5]).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thanks for <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Latourea">Latourea</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> you are no doubt right.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Am glad you liked the <name key="Labichea">Labichea</name>. Yes, it is a great pity that Rchb. f. would not publish a revision of either genera or species of Orchids. I urged him to do so over &amp; over again before Gen. Plant.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</p>
               </note> should be forced to undertake it. He has suspended all communication with Kew, why I cannot conceive except that we did the Orchids for Genera without him! — He is an unaccountable creature.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thanks for the article on Genera names<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B84.03.01?</p>
               </note> — I have not digested it yet, being frightfully busy.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever sincerely yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jos <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>D. Hooker</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Bentham is back — very low &amp; weak.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dendrobium%20superbiens">Dendrobium superbiens</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Labichea">Labichea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Latourea">Latourea</name>
            </p>
         </div>
